\begin_layout Section*
Geographic Distribution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Global Distribution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\shape italic
Vespa tropica
\shape default
 is found in China, Japan, Malaysia, Hong Kong, Singapore, India, and the
 Philippines 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "GBIF"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Guam Distribution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To date, there have been eleven sightings of 
\emph on
V.
 tropica
\emph default
, all in central Guam (Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Vespa-tropica-sightings"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Control Recommendations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Guam distribution of 
\emph on
V.
 tropica
\emph default
 indicates that island-wide eradication is not feasable.
 If a 
\emph on
V.
 tropica
\emph default
 nest is discovered, it should be left alone unless it is in a high risk
 area such as immediately adjacent to a home or school.
 Nest removal is dangerous and should be attempted only by experienced pest
 control operators.
\end_layout

